race.comment: SLEEPY JOE (10) is fast and spiked her figures when finishing just a head from the winner over 1200m at Warwick. She will skip across and the shorter sprint should be an issue. Just has to hold the form to go close. MISHANI HERCULES (4) was outgraded last time in a rich feature at the Gold Coast but had been threatening prior. Has the inside barrier and is a live chance. BUSH BATTLE (9) peaks and the former Victorian is on the improve. Finished closer than the market anticipated at Rockhampton following a narrow defeat this trip as favourite at Roma. He's been freshened and also has claims. CALL SIGN (2) resumes for a new stable and has been racing over longer at metro level. Has the blinkers on for the first time and may be forward this time around. The betting will be key.
